Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) and social network analysis (SNA) in analyzing textual data and social networks, which are both relevant to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also touches on the visualization of social networks, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the organization and processing of information, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of semantic maps, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL).
